Police arrested three alleged hijackers yesterday near the Grayston off-ramp following a shootout. JOHANNESBURG - Police say they're interrogating three suspects arrested in a shootout with officers on the M1 highway to try and trace the fourth suspect.The alleged hijackers were arrested yesterday near the Grayston off-ramp; one of them was wounded.Police say the men are also linked to a string of robberies in KwaZulu-Natal.The police's Kay Makhubele says they will now face additional charges, including robbery, attempted murder and hijacking.&quot;Interrogating the other suspects is part of our investigation and at the moment we haven't got a lead of his whereabouts but a manhunt is underway for him.&quot;WATCH: Cops arrest 3 in Sandton shootout